---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Work" description="What I have been doing lately - Felipe Lamarca">
  <div class="space-y-12">
    <header>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">My Work</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">What I have been doing lately</p>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-8">
      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
          Data Scientist <span class="text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">@</span> <a href="https://atlasintel.org/" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AtlasIntel</a>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          AtlasIntel provides advanced data products for political intelligence and economic forecasting. I'm currently working on calibrating survey samples, political analysis, public opinion monitoring, and improving internal data pipelines.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
          Researcher <span class="text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">@</span> <a href="https://mape.org.br/" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MAPE</a> <span class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 text-base font-normal">(IESP-UERJ)</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          MAPE is the Policy and Election Monitoring and Evaluation Laboratory, coordinated by Fernando Meireles (IESP-UERJ) and Bruno Schaefer (IESP-UERJ). We are dedicated to studying public policy, elections, and their interconnections. Our goal is to improve academic production on the topic and decisively influence public debate. Specifically, we combine different methodologies to study policy and elections, including causal inference and machine learning techniques.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
          Researcher <span class="text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">@</span> <a href="https://www.lab-doxa.org.br/" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">DOXA</a> <span class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 text-base font-normal">(IESP-UERJ)</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          DOXA is the Laboratory of Electoral Studies, Political Communication and Public Opinion, coordinated by Argelina Cheibub Figueiredo (IESP-UERJ). The laboratory is a leading center for research in political communication in Brazil. It is dedicated to the study of electoral processes and political communication, producing theses, dissertations, publications, and analyses across topics such as electoral advertising, political journalism, political attitudes, and voting behavior. More recently, it has expanded its scope to include the analysis of electoral results, broadening its research agenda and incorporating scholars dedicated to the study of elections.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        Before joining AtlasIntel, MAPE, and DOXA, I provided data science and research consulting services to both industry (Roberto Marinho Foundation, Artplan, Visagio) and academia (FGV EBAPE, CEBRAP, GENI/UFF). Please check my <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1dFBrI109flg6zSQHnFIxUd1DRfieCYAT/view" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CV</a> for more information on my work experience.
